name: Barnes & Noble University of Delaware Bookstore
directions: If entering front door off of Main Street, restrooms are immediately to your right. If you pass the cafe counter, you've gone too far.
comment: There are 3 restrooms. The 1 marked "Men's" and the one marked "Women's" both have 3-4 stalls, including 1 handicap accessible stall. The 3rd bathroom is an accessible single-stall restroom intended for all/any/no gender and it includes a changing table.

name: Green River Coffee Company
directions: There are two of them in the back of the coffee house dining area, both all genders.
comment: Staff is friendly and will let you use the restroom.

name: Temple Coffee
directions: Located to the left of counter, down hallway
comment: Key attached to tin on counter by hallway

name: Chaco Canyon Organic Cafe
comment: No need to be a customer; just ask for the code.

name: Marlow's Tavern
directions: Back right corner
comment: Two gender neutral single stalls

name: OUTSaskatoon
directions: Third floor, accords from the community centre. Must request a key from someone in the community centre.
comment: Two locked bathrooms. The centre itself offers great LGBT+ resources, worth checking it out.

name: Hooded Merganser Restaurant
directions: first left down the hooded merganser hall, beside the men's room
comment: no one cares if ur a customer or not just ask the hostess where the bathrooms are

name: Zzest Cafe
directions: In the back
comment: Very friendly staff and great food!

name: Funky Sweets
directions: Back of cafe

name: Changing Perceptions
directions: Through the caf√©'s arch way, up the steps and to your left. If you can't climb steps there is a ramp at the rear entry of South Street car park. Go down it and straight through the workshop, out the doors and it's on your right.
comment: Just pretend to browse the furniture for a bit and you'll be fine!

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store behind electronics by the pick up desk

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store behind electronics at the pick up area

name: Deception Pass - Scenic Vista Parking
directions: On the Whidbey Island (western) end of the DP Bridge, there's a parking lot. The restrooms are on the inland side.
comment: 4 non-accessible, 2 accessible single-stalls.

name: The Frederick Coffee Company and Cafe
Target
directions: In front of the registers, left of the Pizza Hut.
comment: Accessible family bathroom

name: Rankin Science West
directions: Make sure you're in the westernmost section of the building. The entrance nearest these bathrooms is across from the expression tunnel nearest the pond. There's one of these private bathrooms on every floor of the west wing in the corner near the elevator.
comment: It's a small room with a single stall and a sink/mirror, but the outermost door can be locked to make it a completely private bathroom.

name: Union Square Donuts
directions: By the tables in the front

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store

name: Ben & Jerry's Ice Cream
directions: In the back. It's a small store, so it's straight ahead from the front door.

name: SuperValu
directions: In the rear corner of the store, by the dairy section. Head back into the weird hallway and the restrooms will be on your left.

name: Go Chicken Go
directions: Outside on the south side of the building
comment: Ask employees for the key

name: Hooch and Banter
comment: For customers

name: CVS Pharmacy
directions: In the back, to the left of the pharmacy counter

name: Milk Jar Cookies
directions: in the back hallway
comment: you have to be a paying customer

name: Caffe acri
comment: Have to be a customer

name: Pita Pit
directions: Straight to the back
comment: Sign says "Our restrooms are for customers only".

name: Leavitt Family Dentistry
directions: In the front door, directly across the waiting room and hall
comment: It is not necessary to be a patient. Reminder that it may be awkward if you're a socially conscious/anxious person to just come and leave.

name: John Storvik Park
directions: Near the little "Spray Pad" squirter area & the big playground area, in a small building.
comment: Unless you cine a small stool built jutting out from the wall, there isn't a changing table.

name: Kiwanis Thrift Shop - Anacortes
directions: To the right of the main entrance, in a corner (may need to go around some shelves and stuff).
comment: The changing table is a folded table, which can be set up with a bit of effort (might need to ask for help if you can't set it up). The sign doesn't have the accessible symbol, but it appears to be - just be aware.

name: The Haus Coffeeshop
directions: In the back right, behind the partition
comment: It's a caf√©, so use your own buying-etiquette. Everything there is great, I can say.

name: Cafe morocco
directions: Hallway in back
comment: They're thinking about making them gender neutral so if you want to mention it and encourage them to do so...

name: Potbelly Samdwich Shop
directions: All the way at the back of the shop.

name: Multco Aging, Disability, & Veteran's Services
directions: Second floor, directly across from stairs a bit to the left.
comment: This is a state benefits office but as far as I know anybody can walk in and use the bathroom without being questioned.

name: Half Price Books
directions: In the back. By the clearance.

name: 7-Eleven
directions: Through the front door and turn left.
comment: One single private gender-neutral room with handrails for mobility assistance.

name: Bridge Pizza
comment: It's a restaurant, so you should probably be ordering something

name: Brattleboro Memorial Hospital
directions: If you enter the ER, there is an all gender bathroom immediately to your right. You can go in there without having to check in or anything.
comment: All the bathrooms in the ER are for all genders, so if you need care (especially overnight) this may be a good place to go.

name: Home Depot
directions: Right by the other bathrooms to the far right near the lumber
comment: Single stall, marked a s "family bathroom"

name: Downtown Local
directions: In the back of the shop, to the right
comment: Just act like you're browsing

name: Home
directions: I just go in and use the bathroom. It's at my house.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back room of the cafe, on the north wall. There's a second entrance a couple feet north of the main one - if you use it, the bathrooms (gendered, single toilet) are on the right and you bypass the counter altogether.

name: Starbucks
directions: To the left, then down the small hallway on the right. Two gendered single toilet rooms.
comment: Just head back casually, you don't need a key and they don't seem to track who's a customer or not.

name: Modern Love Restaurant
directions: Toward the back on the left past the kitchen
comment:
For restaurant customers.
https://www.facebook.com/ModernLoveOmaha/

name: Summerville Behavioral Health
directions: In the waiting room. Enter through the front door and turn right, can't miss it.
comment: You have to be a client.

name: Kay Cleaners
directions: Ask to use the bathroom. It's located in the back.
comment: You don't need to be a paying customer.

name: Kay Cleaners
directions: Ask to use the bathroom. It's located in the back.
comment: You don't need to be a paying customer, but they also may not have soap.

name: Kay Cleaners
directions: Walk in and ask to use the bathroom.
comment: You don't have to be a customer. There is 1 single person bathroom.

name: Kay Cleaners
directions: Walk in and ask to use the bathroom in the back. You will not be denied. We offer use to non paying and paying people alike.
comment: There's only one bathroom per location, so groups would have to wait.

name: Java Jive
directions: Single gender neutral restroom. Can be a line for it. Straight back from the front door and to the left next to the bookshelf.

name: Keefe Campus Center (Amherst College)
directions:
Basement: take a right when coming down the stairs, and a right at the end of the hall, bathroom will be on your right. 
2nd floor: exit elevator and look to your right, will be in an alcove with a Men's bathroom and an office.
comment: Single user bathroom on the 2nd floor (accessible by elevator) and one in the basement (not accessible by elevator)

name: Vita Cucina Bakery
directions: Back of bakery
comment: No sinage re: customer status

name: Pet Supplies Plus
directions: Back of the store through grey double doors.
comment: Ask any associate and they will be more than happy to direct you.

name: Tabletop Board Game Cafe
comment: You have to be a paying customer....but play a few board games and have fun.

name: Paludan caf√©
directions: Upstairs to the left.

name: Century Arden 14 and XD
directions: Behind admissions.
comment: Behind admissions. Must have a ticket.

name: Plattsville Pizza
directions: It's in the very back of the store.
comment: You should be a paying customer, then just ask an employee if you can use the washroom.

name: Quickly Tea
directions: Very back, end of hallway, to the left
comment: Have to be a customer

name: Dunkin Donuts
directions: All the way to the right, around a corner.
comment: C'mon, it's donuts.

name: Indochino
directions: First floor behind front desk, directly across from entrance
comment: Single stall

name: Petco
directions: Straight towards the back of the store on the right next to the water fountains.
comment: Will have no issues. Two individual single bathrooms with locks. Employees are cool. Plus I work here in the grooming salon. (Ftm)

name: Petco
directions: Walk through front doors, straight towards the back, on the right near the water fountains.
comment: Two individual Single bathrooms with lock.

name: Starbucks
directions: Right in front of you as soon as you walk in.

name: Vedge Caf√©
directions: all the way back
comment: you have to be  paying customer

name: Appalachian Mountain Brewery
directions: Turn right when you walk in the front door.

name: TLC Coffee
directions: Right by the back door
comment: I have it as inaccessible because I am not a wheelchair user and am not sure how difficult it would be so would rather not judge that. There aren't stairs or handle bars in the restroom. It's a single stall for anyone.

name: Watts Street Baptist Church
directions: On all three floors, signs around the building specifically giving you directions to gender neutral restrooms

name: Grandpa Mac
directions: To the right of where you order food. Walk past the counter and go down the corridor. You will turn to see two single stall bathrooms each marked unisex.
comment: Bathrooms are accessible and have changing tables. Restaurant has vegan and gluten free options as well.

name: Veteran's Memorial Park Pool and Ice Arena
directions: Two family locker rooms with toilet facilities straight ahead as you enter the lobby.

name: Linda's Tavern
directions: In the main bar, next to the board games
comment: This is a bar so you'll need to be 21 and have ID on the weekends
